# Task Completion Workflow

Before marking a task complete:

1. Confirm scope and acceptance signals are met.
2. Confirm behavior was validated with relevant checks.
3. Update docs affected by behavior or process changes.
4. For **user-visible** work, set **`metadata.releaseNoteSummary`** on the task (via **`update-task`**) before **`complete`** — one sentence adopters should read; see **`src/modules/documentation/instructions/release-notes-authoring.md`**. Internal/chore tasks may omit it.
5. Record evidence references for risky/release-impacting changes.
6. Capture follow-up work instead of hiding residual risk.
7. Close any open subagent sessions linked to this task using `close-subagent-session` before transitioning.


